  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted across all five flow-speed operating points; sensitivity of the relative hemolysis index to inlet boundary conditions, fluid viscosity, and rotor clearance was explored via Latin hypercube sampling. Results of that UQ campaign are summarised in the validation narrative and informed the acceptance decision.",
