      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FDA pump hemolysis benchmark validation — 5-point operating map",
      "description": "CFD predictions of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA benchmark experimental data at five flow-speed combinations. RH < 1 achieved at all operating points. The accompanying UQ campaign (Latin hypercube, 200 samples) demonstrated that RH sensitivity to inlet velocity uncertainty (±5%) and fluid viscosity (±8%) remained below 0.04 RH units across all conditions, confirming robustness of the worst-case identification."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-02-mesh-independence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh independence study — three-level Richardson extrapolation",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (2.1 M, 6.4 M, 18.7 M cells) assessed via Richardson extrapolation. Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH < 2.3% on fine mesh. Discretization error contribution to total uncertainty budget is negligible relative to model-form uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-predicate-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Predicate device hemolysis comparison — relative hemolysis index",
      "description": "Relative hemolysis index computed for investigational device versus predicate across all 5 operating points. All RH values satisfy RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Worst-case operating condition identified at 3 L/min, 3500 RPM with RH = 0.81 (95% CI: 0.74–0.88 from UQ campaign)."
    }
  ],
